# Reduce the data set to remove the fire event and any site-years with insufficient data. 
Based on geographic proximity, we will remove sites (1) "SUE" (redundant with "USC"), (2) "LAG" (redundant with "EST") and (3) "Weir" (redundant with "LSC") from all subsequent analysis. We also remove all years from the remaining sites where "percent complete" (of the Jun 1 to Oct 31 time series) is less than the 65% threshold. Note: A full Jun 1 - Oct 31 record is 153 days and 65% of this summer period is approx 100 days. We also remove all data from the year 2020 as this is the disturbance year and not representative of either the pre- or post-fire periods.

The last bit of this chunk exports a copy of the final "Analysis-Ready" data set (file "CZU_StreamTemp_Cleaned_Final.csv"), saving it to the working directory. This is a professional standard for ensuring reproducibility and providing a clean hand-off for colleagues and/or reviewers. This is the data set that should be used for all analyses.

```{r Data screening and filtering}
# Identify valid site-year pairs based on the 65% threshold
valid_years <- completeness_summary %>%
  filter(percent_complete >= 65) %>%
  select(site, year)

# Filter the master dataframe
